We need to be HANDS DOWN the best damage dealers in pick-up groups. I don't mean that we can kill things in two hits, that would be horribly overpowered and I think that's what Verant is trying to stay away from.<br>
What I want is for Wizzies to have the BEST damage per second in multiple battles. I think maybe huge, clunky nukes would serve this purpose, only with Draught-style mana efficiency and quad-Lure style casting times. This way, the Wizard is doing something very useful to the group by dealing out huge damage amounts, but Wizzies couldn't use a 24-second nuke while soloing (/imagines himself trying to solo a frost giant with this). This would prevent Wizzies from abusing their power for personal benefit.<br>
I'd make up mana/casting time/damage stats for my new &quot;several thousand ton meteor spell,&quot; but I don't have enough experience in this field.<br>
To summarize:<br>
We need Bane-style damage, Draught-style mana efficiency, and Robe-style casting times. <p>Eamin Whitefalcon <BR> Erudite Wizard <BR> Priest of Solusek Ro <BR> "My ego will smother your ego in its cradle"--Eamin <BR> http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41988</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/15/01 9:26:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Group a Wizard for Crying out Loud (Cleric's perspective</span><hr size=1> First of all, very nice post Grimstaff, except that I might argue that some other non-wizard classes, maybe even clerics as you mentioned, are actually the classes that are a bit out of alignment.<br>
<br>
Jrathek,<br>
<br>
I don't quite agree with the way you've put some things.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It kinda makes me wonder -- If you look at any caster class, not a single class can really be called the damage class. Melees have rogues, but what do casters have as the equivilent?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, first of all, monks and rogues sort of share the Melee damage category.  Both have a small array of supporting abilities(Sneak/hide/poison, feign/mend).<br>
<br>
Second, I look at the four int casters and I see that three are readily capable damage dealers.  The Wizard, the Magician, and the Necromancer.  The Necromancer's ability to do damage is a bit specialized, and the necro has lots of other nifty tricks to pull that don't do any damage directly, so I would rule out Necromancers as a damage dealing class.  So that leaves Wizards and Mages.<br>
<br>
Both these classes seem clearly designed to be able to dish out damage.  <br>
<br>
Magicians have three primary sources of damage:  Pets, Damage shields, and Direct Damage.  Their pets and damage shields are top of the line, and thier Direct Damage is respectable, but doesn't appear to be the forte of the class.  They have less variety of direct damage(virtually no target AE's, a few rains and PBAE's here and there, and a fairly decent array of single target nukes).   Magicians seem to be the hybrid pure damage dealer.  Whatever kind of pure damage the situation calls for, the mage will be able to provide some, and eventually, it should add up to a solid chunk of a groups overall output.  At high levels, this role begins to change somewhat, as two particular summoning spells become more valuable(CoH and Mod Rod.. I've heard great things about the new mod rod, I need to get 56 and find the spell hehe), and their debuff spell becomes more important.  But Mages are still a class loaded with damage dealing potential and little else.  <br>
<br>
Wizards, on the other hand <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> are</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the pure magical damage dealing class.  Compared to other int. casters, even magicians, wizard utility is minimal at best.  Spells like root, stun, and snare round out the class and are much like the secondary abilities of the rogue and the monk because face it, wizards would be damn frustrating to play without those caster basics.  Wizards basically have two things to do:  Nuke and Port.  Look at the wizard spell list..  It is completely loaded with damage spells.  There are single target nukes of varying flavors and a healthy number of AE's, as Rains, PB, or targetable.  A couple spells are there just to let you nuke more, like harvest and concussion.  When it comes to combat, if you aren't called upon to snare, all a wizard does, basically, is deal magical damage and save mana for evac.<br>
<br>
I never really realized it until lately that I've looked at some of my casting logs, but as a magician I spend an awful large amount of mana on spells <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> other</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> than nukes.  In a recent but short(45 minute) trip to the hole I spent about 60% of my mana on nukes, the rest went to damage shields, pets, Malosi and one cast of Call of the Hero.  When I look at a standard wizard spell summary, it's 2 to 5 different nukes, harvest, and concussion unless the wiz is snaring.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think you're wrong that there are no damage dealing casters, it's wizzies and mages.  And for pure damage, it's wizards with a comfortable, but not necessarily spectacular, lead.  Wizards are maybe not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> quite</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as singularly focused on damage as rogues and monks are, but they're not really that far off, especially when compared with other int casters.<br>
<br>
<br>
You make good points that wizards aren't really much like heavy artillery.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Artillery in real life, typically, takes a long time to prepare, takes skill in control and aim, and is vulnerable due to lack of movement. I don't see wizards as that at all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->But I don't quite agree with all of it.  I think that wizards take awhile to prepare(meditation), and take skill to control and aim(choosing appropriate targets and timing to avoid aggro).  Unlike heavy artillery, Wizards are vulnerable due mostly to lack of armored protection, which is a point you made.  <br>
<br>
I think of wizards as something like a bomber.  A mobile but vulnerable target with the power to take out important targets while others protect.  Have you ever played X-wing or TIE fighter?  Often, bombing missions will have the vulnerable bombers destroy the primary target, while the tanks and fighters keep the way clear.  <br>
<br>
Bombers = Y-wings, B-Wings (Wizards, Mages)<br>
Fighters = X-Wings, A-Wings (Rangers, Rogues, Monks)<br>
Tanks = Cruisers, etc. (Warrior/Cleric)<br>
<br>
Of course, wizards can double as Shuttles too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We're the closest there is to a pure magical damage caster, and we can't sustain it. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm not quite sure what you're getting at here.  Of course you can sustain damage.  It's not like you're issued a tank of mana when you log on and that's how much you get to use for the night.  A wizard can sustain damage depending on his mana regeneration rate.  Whether the rate of dealing damage is high enough is debatable, but it is definitely sustainable, should you choose it to be.  But then, you can also control the amount of damage you do over a specific period of time.  Sometimes you nuke harder, sometimes you lay off, and very often this kind of thing can save a group.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> This vision has drifted from what people generally see wizards as, IMO. It seems that we should get long casting, very high damage spells, but instead we're more of a utility class than we should be, IMO. And we're not even specialized at that. Being a taxi is the only thing we do that is really uniquely ours, and druids have a lot of that ability <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm not exactly sure what you're trying to say here.  However, I do think it would be cool to have like, a 25 second mega blast with high damage and a good ratio.  But if you think of wizards as the bomber rather than the stationary artillery, such an ability isn't really necessary, although it could fit.  I really don't think wizards have too much utility..  One <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> can</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> take the view that the utility is a downside, but I prefer to think of the utility a wizard has(other than teleports) as merely options that can spice up the class, should a wizard choose to use them.  A wizard that isn't needed for snare, root, or stun can put 100% of his resources towards dealing damage.  What other caster does that consistantly?  A mage is the only one that comes close.<br>
<br>
 <p><hr align="left"  width="100%">

