<br>
What does that mean? 3 classes are used by players as the bare basic bones of the large majority of exp groups, leaving the other 12 of us to fight for the remaining 3 slots. <br>
<br>
Let's examine this skeletal group and see what it brings to the table:<br>
You have a player that can hold aggro while taking efficient damage while dealing good damage himself. You are able to haste that player, slow down the damage he takes, and up the mana regen of his cleric who has the groups heals locked down rather nicely. What do we need now? We need snare and damage. Who's the highest damage dealer that we could get for this group? Rogues, followed now by monks. We still need snare, what class would best fit this role and still add to the groups efficiency? Hmm hard call, you now have about 4-5 classes fighting for this one spot.<br>
<br>
The Ideal group that I would take to sebilis if I were an enchanter.<br>
1. me(enchanter)*I'm not really an enchanter, but let's pretend*<br>
2.cleric<br>
3.rogue<br>
4.rogue<br>
5.rogue<br>
6. shadowknight to tank/snare/out-taunt the rogues<br>
<br>
Look at it anyway you like, but the fact remains that some classes in this game are heavily favoured by verant for the exp game, and it's not our own lack of power that keeps us from groups, but rather it is the sheer overpowering of these 3 main classes for an aspect of the game that we are all forced to deal with... the exp grind. 3 of the 15 classes effectively lock down, far more efficiently than any others, 70% of what is required to advance in this game by the large majority of its content. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=10196.topic&start=121&stop=122>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=10879.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=10840.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=10196.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcomp